BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Cadillac Crew
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261023T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261023T213000
DTSTAMP:20260708T065306Z
UID:occ-468@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Tori Sampson's drama: four activists in a Virginia civil right
 s office ask whether the movement's equality includes women.\n\nTori Samps
 on's play unfolds in a Virginia civil rights office on the day of a much-a
 nticipated Rosa Parks speech\, where four activists start asking whether t
 he movement's promise of equality extends to women. It reclaims the storie
 s of the overlooked organizers behind desegregation\, with more humor than
  the setup suggests. Karlotta Washington directs for the Conyers Rockdale 
 Council for the Arts. Runs through October 25.
GEO:33.6671075;-84.0180229
LAST-MODIFIED:20260708T063625Z
LOCATION:Conyers Rockdale Council for the Arts\, 910 Center St NE
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://conyersarts.org/calender-of-events/cadillac-crew/
END:VEVENT
